   Vulnerable Line: PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefault("add_module");
   Reason: The code is vulnerable to command injection as it directly passes user-controlled input to the PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefault function without proper validation or sanitization. An attacker could potentially inject malicious commands here.

3. Vulnerability Type: Memory Leak
   Vulnerable Line: auto session = new FastCGISession(...);
   Reason: The code dynamically allocates memory for the FastCGISession object using the new keyword but does not free the memory using delete. This can lead to memory leaks in the application.

4. Vulnerability Type: Unhandled Exception
   Vulnerable Line: catch (std::system_error& e) { return; }
   Reason: The catch block catches a std::system_error exception but does not handle it appropriately. Simply returning from the catch block without any further action may lead to unexpected behavior or resource leaks. It is recommended to log the error or handle it properly.

